window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Time may be many things, but it is definitely not on our side.</p> <p>It always wins, no matter how much we struggle against it.</p> <p><i>Tales Out of Time: Writer on Demand, Vol. 3</i> includes four stories:</p> <ul> <li>\"Standing Still\" (approximately 4,600 words) tells the story of one man trying to help another deal with the reality in which he finds himself. The story originally appeared in Time Twisters, edited by Jean Rabe and Martin H. Greenberg (DAW Books, Inc. 2007).</li> <li>\"Knowing She Would\" (approximately 3,600 words) tells the story of a girl visited repeatedly by those who need her help in their journeys. The story originally appeared in \"Historical Hauntings\", edited by Jean Rabe and Martin H. Greenberg (DAW Books, Inc. 2000).</li> <li>\"A Passion for Time Travel\" (approximately 3,900 words) deals with the problems of a company that sells vacations throughout time. The story originally appeared in TimeShares, edited by Jean Rabe and Martin H. Greenberg (DAW Books, Inc. 2010).</li> <li>\"Future Futures\" (approximately 4,325 words) deals with the business and politics of data mining the future. It originally appeared in Apollo's Daughters, edited by Bryan Young (Silence in the Library 2014).</li> </ul> <p>About the author:</p> <p>Donald J. Bingle has published a wide variety of books (including the Dick Thornby Thriller series) and more than 70 published stories, primarily in themed and tie-in anthologies. He also wrote adventures for the Timemaster role-playing game.</p> <p>Donald J. Bingle is a member of the International Thriller Writers, Horror Writers Association, International Association of Media Tie-In Writers, and the Origins Game Fair Library. More about Don can be found at www.donaldjbingle com or follow him on social media @donaldjbingle.</p>"; 
